How to run demo:
##################################################
### AGL receiver side:

Build and flash agl branch dab_4.0.2.xml
Copy python files from CastScreen_receiver_agl dir to AGL
Modify /etc/xdg/weston.ini on AGL to match CastScreenDemo/weston.ini

systemctl restart weston # to apply weston.ini

Connect AGL to the same network with Android board

python CastScreen_receiver_agl/wayland_receiver.py

###################################################
### Ubuntu receiver side:

python CastScreen_receiver_agl/cs_receiver.py
###################################################
### Android sender side:

adb root
adb shell setprop persist.enable_task_snapshots false
### To prevent memory leak when opening multiple apps

adb install -r -g -t sender.apk

Ensure wayland_receiver.py is running on AGL and sender is in same subnet as receiver

Start castscreen on android. Two ways:

./start_castscreen_with_ip.sh [AGL_RECEIVER_IP]

or

Using android app gui:
- Start CastScreen app.
- Select receiver
- Press start
- Use keyboard (Tab & Enter keys) to navigate through confirmation dialog
- Cast screen should be running now

To cast google maps:

./start_maps_virtual.sh [VIRTUAL_DISPLAY_ID]

#Launch google maps on virtual display
#VIRTUAL_DISPLAY_ID is shown in android application
